cs.HC, cs.NE, cs.LG, cs.CB, cs.SD 

This paper involves the use of electrical biosignals to control a video game, which falls under the category of human-computer interaction (cs.HC). The use of machine learning methods for signal processing suggests a focus on neural engineering (cs.NE) and machine learning (cs.LG). The evaluation of muscular activity also suggests a possible connection to computational biology (cs.CB) and signal processing (cs.SD).
